name: Thille Park public restrooms
comment: There's four gender-neutral, single-person bathrooms next to the playground in the park. Each bathroom has a sink. I don't remember if there are changing tables, but I would assume so because it's right next to the playground. There's no parking lot, but there's street parking available. You can see the bathrooms on Google Maps Street View on Thille St.

name: Andrea
directions: Woodland Hills Recreation Center
comment: The bathrooms are located on an outside wall of the main recreation-center building. There are at least 6 bathrooms (separate doors for each bathroom), but none of them have sinks. The sinks are built into the wall next to the bathroom doors. I'm pretty sure at least one of the bathrooms has a changing table, but some don't. You could probably call the recreation center to find out for sure if there are changing tables. There's a public parking lot (free parking) right next to the building. There's another two sink-on-the-outside-wall bathrooms by one of the baseball fields nearby. Very clean bathrooms.
